[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to determine why I can't place the `bcprov` jar on the bootstrap via tests. The public API doesn't allow it, and calling `new BouncyCastlePQCProvider()` under a custom SecurityManager isn't possible. I can't use reflection to call private methods either, nor create a subclass with a null class loader. There are concerns with `Provider previousProvider = Security.getProvider` being globally mutable, especially if tests run in parallel. Adding synchronization might help, but I’m uncertain about that.
