 issue but noted no metadata is allowed. It seems like including it in the final version could cause confusion if we acknowledge it’s present yet unmodified. I should probably leave it alone since we didn’t create it, and I don't want to risk deleting anything important. I'll also consider if we can cover any uncovered parts using the public API, but that might be tricky.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining class loader issues**\\n\\nI’m considering whether `Class.getClassLoader` for application classes might return null. In SubstrateVM, there are limited class loaders, and often, app classes rely on the application class loader. Native Image can return either platform or app class loader, and if it's null, `Class.forName` could work in native runs, but I have doubts about dynamic reporting in native test compilation. The reports came from earlier tests without a constructor. I should note that `Class.forName` may not be directly reachable, but I need to tread lightly on how much I say about that.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing BouncyCastle provider issue**\\n\\nI'm trying to determine why I can't place the `bcprov` jar on the bootstrap via tests. The public API doesn't allow it, and calling `new BouncyCastlePQCProvider()` under a custom SecurityManager isn't possible. I can't use reflection to call private methods either, nor create a subclass with a null class loader. There are concerns with `Provider previousProvider = Security.getProvider` being globally mutable, especially if tests run in parallel. Adding synchronization might help, but I’m uncertain about that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for the active class.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/BouncyCastlePQCProviderTest.java`\n  - Instantiates `BouncyCastlePQCProvider`, which exercises `loadAlgorithms(...)`.\n  - Verifies Rainbow and McEliece mappings are loaded through the provider’s public API.\n  - Registers/removes the provider via `Security` and restores any previous provider.\n- Removed placeholder test:\n  - `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/Bcprov_jdk15onTest.java`\n\nNotes:\n- Did not modify or generate reachability metadata.\n- Did not run tests locally, per instruction not to compile/run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f0bf5f27f694902016a10b0c7ef3c8197bb41404f608c3148\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 619, "output": 870, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22993, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779478714203, "responseId": "resp_0f0bf5f27f694902016a10b0baa7508197a7ba000018df917e"}}
